  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for church-led peacebuilding in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Increased effectiveness of the SSCC Action Plan for Peace. This project will contribute towards creating an enabling environment for human rights, as part of the wider APP.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Workshops with SSCC and partners to develop capacity building framework. Conduct training for SSCC staff/facilitators in delivering the framework. 
- Work with SSCC and partner in standardising training curriculum corresponding to each APP pillar. Rolling out this training to ICCs as per capacity building framework. Translate, print and disseminate the training materials.
- Develop Terms of Reference and standing Agenda for regional ICC forums. Convene regional ICC forums for two regions (Bahr el Ghazal and Upper Nile).
- Support the re-establishment of SSCC Upper Nile regional office in coordination with other APP partners.
- Conduct scoping visits and needs assessments to determine target areas for APP support. 
- Pilot innovative ways of reaching remote or mobile communities, or groups with low levels of literacy through use of technology.
- Conduct training/analysis with SSCC Advocacy Taskforce (including context analysis, strategy development, and drafting a six-month work plan to be presented to SSCC Executive Committee for approval).</narrative>
  </description>
